title: Great app terrible businesses associated
text: I think the app is truly a great concept and it can definitely help both businesses and consumers. However in my experience using the app some businesses are essentially using the service to turn trash into profit rather than potential waste into a decent meal. Prices vary based on business some businesses charge $10 for literal scraps. There needs to be some sort of quality control or some sort of requirement. I shouldn’t have to toss out the food they give because it’s just inedible. We should be able to leave visible reviews on the restaurants we ordered from so there’s more transparency. After having 2 bad experiences in a row I cannot be the only one feeling like with the popularity of the app abuse is inevitable. If a visible review is shared on the app I think it would keep businesses more honest and prevent a bit of nonsense. I don’t expect the best of the best or an over abundance but I definitely don’t want to pay $5-10 then come home and throw away inedible food.

title: Surprise box

title: Charged after reporting issue of nothing to save at pick up
text: Contacted support because the place I went for pick again didn’t have anything. Reach out to report no food. Then was charged 4.99 for an order I never got. Bot response to contact message explain that the restaurant should have said there was no food. I want a refund. Still waiting on response. Contact my bank and canceling the app. Too many bad experiences at this point. Get better support or better contact between app and restaurant l.

I hate paying full price and I have no problem getting food at the end of the day or one day later. Same thing that happens at my house on a daily occurrence, right? The people who want to buy it, and it helps the restaurants willing to sell it! It’s a win-win!

title: Hit or Miss, but great fun!
text: The restaurants are hit or miss, but it’s a great way to try out new restaurants and bakeries (lots of bakeries!) for minimal cost. I already found some new favorite places. However, the app needs to offer an easy function for restaurants to refund customers when they don’t have anything available, instead of making customers show up and not get anything and then have to contact support to get a refund.

title: OBSESSED
text: Absolutely love this app. The idea of food waste truly haunts me and we see all those photos of famous brands throwing out hundreds of perfectly edible products. Too good to go helps lower the impact of food waste AND allows you to get delicious fresh goods for a significantly lower price!! It’s amazing, try it for sure.

title: Questionable value
text: I imagine this concept will become a phenomenon over the next few years, and I am all for it. Quality and quantity varies. Most merchants are not providing the value listed, but closer to the value paid. I really hope that will change because I have felt cheated more than once. Other times, restaurants have been inconsistent. It’s a big reflection on the app, and I’m hoping the issue will be dealt with before I purchase another meal.
